Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%grams}. Cut the @Lime{1} into wedges.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @Basmati Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

While the rice cooks, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams}. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

While the beef cooks, halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a board. Cut into 1cm chunks.

Pop the avocado into a #small bowl{}, drizzle with some @olive oil{}, squeeze in some lime juice from a lime wedge, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together. Set the avocado salsa aside.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Cajun Spice Mix{1%sachet}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams} and the @Water{50%ml} and @Sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Add less Cajun spice if you'd prefer things milder.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%mins}. Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @Butter{20%grams} until melted, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a good squeeze of lime juice from a lime wedge.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}. Spoon over the mince and top with the cheese and avocado salsa. Serve any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!